metadata.name: Warped #18
metadata.description:
A free little toy.  Play with it and it might make art!  This is my second project using a shader.  It starts by making a simple drawing, then the shader uses noise to warp the image.  I'm making it free because 1) You really have to work at it to make art (but I think it's a lot of fun to tinker with!), and 2) the capture sometimes has minor variances from the final image - couldn't figure it out.  Made with p5js and uses some Perlin noise code by Inigo Quilez.  

After opening, press "s" to save a large jpg.

metadata.name: Mustachioed #65
metadata.description:
Who has the chance to have a weird mustache on his face?
Art, personality, politics, religion, power or any other factor has made some mustache models dependent on individuals and takes its name from its first or most famous owner.

metadata.name: Helix #10
metadata.description:
"Helix" is a 100% code generative real time 3D sculpture. An interactive study to lighting and color. Move your mouse to set the light's position. Press the "V" key to view the object from different angles (rotation)

CONTROLS

KEYS:
- V: Render a different view (object view angle) on each key press
- B: Toggle Backlight (on/off)
- S: Save a png file
- R: Reset/reload
- SPACEBAR: Toggle light's position auto-update and also toggle (enable/disable) mouse move interactivity

MOUSE:
- Move: Moves (set) the light's position
- Click: Toggle light's position auto-update and mouse move interactivity (the same as the SPACEBAR)

----
Made with p5js (use WebGL canvas)

© May 2023  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: [radials.v1.1] #37
metadata.description:
CHANGELOG: fixed broken sandbox. import from cdn was being blocked by ipfs and did not realize this until post-mint.

---

radial motion mixed with targeted easing and color lerping.
post-processed with a pair of glitch shaders.
lovingly crafted with p5.js

note: there are a lot of particles at play here - please be patient while it renders. should only take a few minutes.

part of the #objkt4objkt 2024 event.

---

press '1' to toggle shaders on/off.
press 's' to save a high-quality image to your computer.

---

resolution: 2000x2000
format: png
libraries: p5.js
